main event: A sighting occurred near El Centro, California on May 23, 1952, involving an object that was observed both visually and by radar.
interesting points: The sighting took place at approximately 3:15 AM., Some observers thought they saw a meteor while others disagreed., The report mentions several possible conclusions including balloon, aircraft, or astronomical., The location of the event is classified., The report is part of Project Blue Book, which investigated UFOs in the 1950s.
sighted object: unknown object possibly mistaken for a meteor
